column5: Federal Register / Vol. 76, No. 123 / Monday, June 27, 2011 / Proposed Rules

column6: DEPARTMENT OF ENERGY / 10 CFR Part 430 / [Docket Number EERE–2011–BT–STD– 0011] / RIN 1904–AC06
Energy Conservation Program: Energy Conservation Standards for Residential Furnaces and Residential Central Air Conditioners and Heat Pumps

column5: 1/10/13 - BAW - efficiency & compatible system table revisions + addition of 2015 standard version
1/10/13 - SAC - reformat table to new syntax, combine standard versions into single table and add SysAvail & IsHP flags
5/20/13 - BAW -added ductless systems, Standard Design column
8/6/13 - SAC - added Show Multi-Speed Compressor column
9/3/2013 - MJB turned on more SysAvail options
column30: Need Std Design system col (especially for no cooling)

column5: 12/9/13 - specification of standard systems for Evap systems
4/22/14 - SAC - added PropEqStd column and also the new AirToWaterHeatPump & GroundSourceHeatPump equipment types
1/26/15 - MJB added rows for other Standards - e.g. 2008 Title-24 and 2006 IECC
1/7/16 - SAC - added rows for new SDHVSplitAirCond & SDHVSplitHeatPump (small duct, high velocity) systems
11/2/18 - SAC - added records for new VCHP (variable capacity HP) equipment
11/13/18 - SAC - revised VCHP records to accept SEER & EER (for reporting only, since not used in simulation)
6/7/19 - SAC - created 2022 codebase (2023 std ver) records - copied from 2019
8/8/19 - SAC - added SetbackTstatReqd return value for CF1R reporting
6/19/20 - SAC - added several new Cooling system types for 2019.2.0, tickets #1225, #1226, #1227 & #1229
8/18/20 - SAC - updated default efficiencies for PkgTerm & SinglePkgTerm ACs (tic #1003)
8/19-20/20 - SAC - added CEER as new efficiency metric associated w/ RoomHP & RoomAC (tic #1003)
08/26/22 - SAC - structural table changes to accommodate SEER2 & EER2 (tic #1331)
08/27/22 - SAC - updated old SEER/EER data and added new SEER2, EER2 and ratios (tic #1331)
08/28/22 - SAC - added SEER2/SEER and EER2/EER efficiency ratios (tic #1331)
09/19/22 - SAC - added SEER2/SEER and EER2/EER efficiency ratios to 2019 code vintage (based on '22) plus '19 SEER2 & EER2 using those ratios (tic #1331)
09/25/22 - SAC - fixed errors in 2022 default EER2s for most system types from 10.2 (EERb) to 11.7 (tic #1331)
11/08/22 - SAC - replaced SEER2/EER2 values in 2019 vintage to be based on '23 standard (rather than calced via multiplier)
11/12/22 - SAC - created 2025 code vint records, copied from 2022 for now
12/11/22 - SAC - switched PropEqStd flag from 1 to 0 for AirToWaterHeatPump for 2022 & 25 vintages (tic #1318)
03/31/23 - SAC - add new system type: HeatPumpDHWCombo - Combined Heating / DHW Heat Pump (tic #1349)
05/16/24 - SAC - add new system type: VCHP3 (tic #1379)
03/05/25 - SAC - add new system type: SplitAirCondPM (tic #1379)
CodeBase - Standard or Code that should be used in the Std Design baseline

column9: Compliance 2014:  valid through December 2014 (with current Federal Air Conditioning efficiency requirements
Compliance 2015:  any time (with 2015 Federal Air Conditioning Requirements)  and solar credit

column5: COP95 - Gas Cooling Efficiency (rated COP for the gas portion)
PPC - Gas Cooling parasitic electric energy at rated conditions (in Watts)
SysAvail - (0/1) flag whether or not the system type is currently implemented in the compliance software
DuctFlag - 1 => requires ducts / 0 => ductless / -1 => may use ducts
IsHP - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not this system type is modeled as a heat pump
Whether or not (1/0) multi-speed compressor is an option
PropEqStd - flag indicating that the proposed design system is to be setup/modeled the same as its corresponding standard design system
StdSystem - system type used to model the standard design
SEERValid - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not the SEER data is valid for the corresponding system type
SEER2Valid - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not the SEER2 data is valid for the corresponding system type
EERValid - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not the EER data is valid for the corresponding system type
EER2Valid - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not the EER2 data is valid for the corresponding system type
CEERValid - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not the CEER data is valid for the corresponding system type
SetbackTstatReqd - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not a setback thermostat is required (based on Res Std section 110.2c)
